description: A slight d'tour from the usual Waterfoot lap to bag the local trig this time. Yeah, I went all those laps without even knowing it was there. I didn't actually count this as a Waterfoot lap because I was trying to save the next milestone to do with Murk. So that, along with the fact that back in 2020 Strava cut out mid-`foot once, means my actual Waterfoot count is what the table says plus two!
